    "display_name": "Drilling Machine",
    "description": "Classification of drill actions using the MLC to detect idle, screw, drilling or percussive drilling states.\n\nThis system provides an example of classifying specific actions rather than simple vibrations, enabling the detection of the operating modes of a common household power drill: screwing, drilling, and percussive drilling, or being stationary. Since motion recognition can be very specific, you can clone this project to retrain it and tailor it to a different drill. To use this example, affix the board firmly to the top side of the drill. Keep in mind that vibrations may dislodge the board, and classification accuracy improves the more securely it is attached to the machine.",
